ASABA – A yet-to-be-identified lady believed to be in her 20s has been murdered by a suspected ritualist in Ogwashi-Uku, Aniocha South Local Government Area of Delta State. Daily Independent gathered that the corpse of the lady was discovered by the roadside, along Ubulu-Unor road, where it was allegedly dumped by a suspected ritualist. It was learnt that the eyes and private organs of the deceased were missing. Community Decries Spate Of Cultism In Delta, Seeks IGP’s… 13-Year-Old Girl Raped To Death In Delta Community Our source who requested anonymity revealed that the body of the deceased was discovered by some passers-by who raised an alarm that attracted the community vigilantes. According to the source, “Some people who passed along the road that early morning saw the corpse of the girl and raised alarm and many people rush down to see for themselves. When we got there, we saw the girl, wearing jean trousers and a white top. Her face was covered in blood, and her two eyes were no more. You can see her eye socket empty”. It was gathered that the vigilantes reached the police who evacuated and deposited the body of the deceased at the community mortuary. When contacted, the Police Public Relation Officer (PPRO) of Delta State police command, DSP Bright Edafe confirmed the killing of the young lady. POLL “The police were alerted to the scene of the incident by community youths who discovered the corpse of the lady with two eyes removed along the road. The DPO in Ogwashi-Uku who also confirmed the incident when contacted said that the corpse has been evacuated to the mortuary” he stated.